The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                               Business Briefs
                              
	 Mumbai, Aug. 26: ABG Shipyard hopes to complete the open offer process for Great Offshore within a months time. The shipbuilder currently holds around nine per cent stake in Great Offshore. Both ABG and its rival Bharati Shipyard have announced open offers for the offshore oil services provider.                             
	 New Delhi, Aug. 26: The contraction in price index was lower at (-) 0.95 per cent for the week ended August 15 compared with (-) 1.53 per cent in the previous week on the back of rising food prices.                             
	 New Delhi, Aug. 26: The government is setting up a high-level task force to address the problems of micro, small and medium enterprises (MSME), which have been demanding adequate financing and other incentives to tackle the slowdown.                             
	 New Delhi, Aug. 26: Auto component maker Motherson Sumi Systems Limited has won orders worth Rs 4,000 crore from European majors, including Volkswagen and BMW, to supply rear view mirrors for six years.                            
	 New Delhi, Aug. 26: Tata Motors will raise about Rs 1,500 crore via fixed deposit schemes, offering up to 9.88 per cent annual interest for a three-year deposit.                                                                                                                           
